### C. Feature Folder Rules

Every feature follows this exact internal structure:

```
features/feature-name/
├── feature-name.routes.ts        ← Lazy-loaded child routes
├── feature-name-list/            ← List/index view
│   ├── feature-name-list.component.ts
│   ├── feature-name-list.component.html
│   └── feature-name-list.component.scss
├── feature-name-detail/          ← Read-only detail view
├── feature-name-form/            ← Create + Edit form (unified)
├── components/                   ← Feature-private sub-components
│   ├── feature-filter-bar/
│   ├── feature-stat-card/
│   └── feature-action-menu/
├── models/
│   └── feature-name.model.ts
└── services/
    └── feature-name.service.ts
```

**Rules:**
- Feature components are never imported directly by other features — only shared components are.
- Cross-feature navigation uses the router — never direct component imports between features.
- A feature's service is `providedIn: 'root'` only if it holds shared state. Otherwise scope to the feature route.
- Delete the `components/` subfolder if the feature has no private sub-components — no empty folders.

